(10068, 615, 'section_title', 'Implement encryption, access control, DLP software, and robust monitoring to prevent and mitigate data leaks.'),
(10069, 615, '_section_title', 'field_66e28a3024921'),
(10070, 615, 'subsection_title', 'What Does it Mean?'),
(10071, 615, '_subsection_title', 'field_66e28a4224922'),
(10072, 615, 'paragraph_1', 'To prevent and mitigate data leaks, implementing encryption, access control, Data Loss Prevention (DLP) software, and robust monitoring is essential. Encryption ensures that both data-at-rest (stored) and data-in-transit (transmitted) remain secure by converting sensitive information into unreadable formats without decryption keys. Access control enforces the principle of least privilege, limiting who can access sensitive data, often using Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) and Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) to reduce unauthorized access risks.<br/><br/>\r\nDLP software helps prevent sensitive information from leaving the organization by monitoring and blocking unauthorized file transfers, whether via email, cloud services, or external devices. Finally, robust monitoring tools like SIEM systems and File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) ensure real-time visibility of data activity, enabling organizations to detect and respond to suspicious actions or potential leaks quickly. Together, these measures form a comprehensive strategy for data protection.'),
